# Code Cleanup Guidelines

## Unused Code Detection

### Imports
- Remove unused imports immediately
- Keep imports organized and grouped:
  ```typescript
  // External imports first
  import { z } from 'zod';
  import { TRPCError } from '@trpc/server';
  
  // Internal imports next
  import { ProductType } from '../entities/product.entity';
  ```
- Remove commented-out imports
- Use specific imports instead of whole modules

### Types and Interfaces
- Remove unused types/interfaces
- If type is only used for Zod schema, use `z.infer<>` instead:
  ```typescript
  // ❌ Don't
  interface ProductInput { ... }
  
  // ✅ Do
  const productSchema = z.object({ ... });
  type ProductInput = z.infer<typeof productSchema>;
  ```

### Variables and Constants
- Remove unused variables
- Remove unused constants
- Check for dead code assignments
- Example from [apps/backend/src/modules/trpc/routers/admin/product.router.ts](mdc:apps/backend/src/modules/trpc/routers/admin/product.router.ts):
  ```typescript
  // ❌ Don't - unused type
  type UpdateProductInput = Partial<CreateProductInput>; // Never used
  
  // ✅ Do - remove if not used
  ```

### Functions and Methods
- Remove unused functions/methods
- Remove empty/stub methods
- Remove commented-out functions
- Check for dead code in functions

### Classes and Components
- Remove unused classes
- Remove unused class members
- Remove empty/stub classes
- Check for dead code in class methods

## Best Practices

### Code Review
- Check for unused code before committing
- Use linter warnings as guidance
- Review entire files when making large changes
- Use IDE tools to detect unused code

### Refactoring
- Remove code instead of commenting out
- Extract reusable code before deletion
- Document why code is preserved if seemingly unused
- Keep related code together

### TypeScript Specific
- Enable strict mode in `tsconfig.json`
- Use `noUnusedLocals` and `noUnusedParameters`
- Check for unused type parameters
- Remove unnecessary type annotations

### Comments
- Remove commented-out code
- Keep only necessary comments
- Update comments when code changes
- Remove TODO comments after completion


